        <c02 level="item" id="d1e197">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>George Madden Martin</persname>to 
                  <persname>Edwin Carty Ranck</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1904 Nov 2</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>6 p. w/env and AMs</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Answers request for autobiographical sketch and
                  picture of herself; expresses appreciation for
                  Ranck's remarks about 
                  <geogname>Kentucky</geogname>writers and her novel, 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Emmy Lou--Her Book and Heart</title></bibref>; mentions recent article in 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The Outlook</title></bibref>by 
                  <persname>Jeanette Leonard
                  Gilder</persname>concerning 
                  <persname>Alice Caldwell Hogan Rice</persname>and 
                  <persname>George Madden Martin</persname>;
                  autobiographical sketch mentions her birth,
                  childhood, education, health, and husband; discusses
                  publication of 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Emmy Lou</title></bibref>in book form and in 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">McClure's</title></bibref>magazine, the response from readers, and
                  namesakes of 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Emmy Lou</title></bibref>; mentions publication of 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The House of Fulfillment</title></bibref>in serial form in 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">McClure's</title></bibref>and the reviews and sales of first and
                  second editions in book form.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
      </c01>
